    "recap_headline": "Sacred Heart",
    "recap_text": "Smithfield, R.I. \u2013\nSacred Heart used two five-run innings to fuel its offense, but Bryant's early surge and steady scoring proved too much in the loss.\nRecords\nSacred Heart | 4-15 (3-3 MAAC)\nBryant | 14-8 (3-3 AE)\nTop Performers\nRyan Rey\n: 3-4, 2 R, 3 RBI, double\nKyle Cincinnati\n: 2-4, R, double\nCJ Nolan\n: 2-5, 2 R, 2 RBI, double\nRice III: 1-4, R, 2 RBI\nGavin Donohue\n: 1-4, R, RBI\nWill Rudolph\n: 2-4, 2 R, 2 RBI\nPeter Link\n: 0-2, R\nJacob Schmutz\n: 1-4, R, RBI\nPJ Rogan\n: 3.1 IP, 6 H, 6 R (2 ER), 2 SO\nJase Schueller\n: 2.0 IP, 4 H, 3 R (2 ER), 1 SO\nChristian Trantino\n: 0.2 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 2 SO\nHow It Happened\nBryant jumped out to an early lead with three runs in the first and another in the second before Sacred Heart responded in the third inning.\nCJ Nolan\nsingled and later scored on a single from\nRyan Rey\n, while\nKyle Cincinnati\nfollowed with a single and\nPeter Link\ndrew a walk to load the bases.\nWill Rudolph\nthen singled to bring home Cincinnati and Rey, and after\nGavin Donohue\nwalked, Rice delivered a single to score Rudolph and Link, capping a five-run inning.\nBryant answered with a run in the third and broke the game open with four runs in the fourth, followed by two more in the fifth and one in the sixth.\nSacred Heart continued to battle, adding a run in the fourth when Rey and Cincinnati singled before\nJacob Schmutz\ndrove in Rey with a sacrifice fly.\nThe Pioneers mounted another rally in the seventh as Schmutz and Rudolph singled and\nGavin Donohue\ndrove in Schmutz with a base hit. Rice was then hit by a pitch to load the bases before Nolan delivered a two-run double to score Donohue and Rudolph. Rey followed with a double of his own, bringing home Nolan and Rice to cap another five-run inning.\nBryant added two runs in the bottom half of the seventh and secured the win.\nUp Next\nThe Pioneers host New Haven at Veterans Park for their home opener on Tuesday, March 24 at 3 p.m.",
